{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":107851,"duration_api_ms":215603,"num_turns":6,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"afdb2db0-2d45-4abf-a44a-0bb42d70c74c","total_cost_usd":0.5610713999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":28811,"cache_read_input_tokens":81524,"output_tokens":3110,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":28811,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":267,"outputTokens":14867,"cacheReadInputTokens":964349,"cacheCreationInputTokens":73147,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.26247065,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":3110,"cacheReadInputTokens":81524,"cacheCreationInputTokens":28811,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.29860075,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All five amendments identify real, verified bugs. Two amendments (fr-2-467b53d8 and fr-2-b5ae378d) describe the same cancellation-during-backoff bug from different angles — both are valid. The BackendUnavailable→BinaryNotFound mapping (fr-2-77935ca0) is confirmed as a semantic/retryability regression. The process-group kill gap (fr-2-fa361db6) is a real operational defect with a clear fix pattern already in the codebase. The test assertion count mismatch (fr-2-b5e89a50) is a straightforward test correctness issue from changing the stub failure count without updating assertions.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-2-467b53d8","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: engine.rs:4642-4655 passes the original `&error` (e.g. TransportFailure) to `fail_run_result` when cancellation fires during backoff sleep. The test at workflow_engine_test.rs:3870 asserts `failure_class == \"cancellation\"` and will fail because `AppError::InvocationFailed{TransportFailure}` maps to \"transport_failure\", not \"cancellation\". The fix is correct: construct `AppError::InvocationCancelled` and pass that instead."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-77935ca0","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: error.rs:302 blanket-maps every `AppError::BackendUnavailable` to `FailureClass::BinaryNotFound`, which is `RetryRule::terminal()` (max_attempts=1, retryable=false). Multiple adapters return `BackendUnavailable` for transient/auth conditions — missing OPENROUTER_API_KEY (process_backend.rs:1164), 401/403 responses (openrouter_backend.rs:326), GitHub HTTP/JSON errors (github.rs:604-625). These are now all mislabeled as \"binary_not_found\" and made permanently non-retryable. The mapping must be restricted to actual binary-not-found paths."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-b5ae378d","decision":"accept","rationale":"This describes the same cancellation-during-backoff bug as fr-2-467b53d8 and is independently valid. The tokio::select! cancellation branch at engine.rs:4642 falls through to `fail_run_result(&error, ...)` with the prior backend error, causing the test to see \"transport_failure\" instead of \"cancellation\". The suggested fix (return a cancellation error from this branch) is correct."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-fa361db6","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: process_backend.rs:365 calls `signal::kill(Pid::from_raw(pid), signal)` targeting only the direct child PID. No process group is established via pre_exec/setsid/setpgid. The tmux adapter at tmux.rs:992 correctly uses `Pid::from_raw(-pid)` to target the process group. When the direct child spawns subprocesses (claude/codex backends), those grandchildren survive SIGKILL as orphans. This is a real operational defect — the fix pattern already exists in the codebase."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-b5e89a50","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: The stub failure count was changed from 3 to 5 (e.g. StubBackendAdapter::default().with_transient_failure(StageId::Implementation, 5)) but the test assertions at lines 1089, 1157, 1468, and 3084 still assert stage entry count of 4. With 5 transient failures and TransportFailure retry policy allowing 5 max_attempts, the stage will be entered more times than the hardcoded 4. The resume tests will fail because the failed-run portion now has more stage entries."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"07b9a2db-5680-4fbf-a355-3143063cb11e"}
